	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If you just want to <em>use</em> the programs on Windows, just download the Allegro 4.0 DLL (which should be on the same page where you got Pin Eight NES Tools) and put it in the same folder as the exe. You only need MinGW (a version of the GCC compiler toolchain for Windows) if you want to recompile the programs, and you only need other versions of GCC if you want to compile the programs on another platform.

		

